&lt;p&gt;If we need to truncate (modify an array by removing the elements), we have three main ways:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;.splice()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Just remember splice modifies, slice accesses. Negative numbers as first arg indicate index from the end of the array.&lt;/p&gt;
