&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;A system is said to be &lt;strong&gt;concurrent&lt;/strong&gt; if it can support two or more actions in progress at the same time. A system is said to be &lt;strong&gt;parallel&lt;/strong&gt; if it can support two or more actions executing simultaneously.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://shop.oreilly.com/product/9780596521547.do&quot;&gt;The Art of concurrency&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
